
Paris, 18 April 1780. RC in John Thaxters hand (PCC, No. 84, I, f. 467469). printed: Wharton, ed., Dipl. Corr. Amer. Rev., 3:620624.
In this letter, received by Congress on 19 Feb. 1781, John Adams provided newspaper accounts regarding a petition by Swedish merchants calling on their King to provide protection for their commerce and the Kings granting of their wish, as well as the formal communication of the declaration of armed neutrality to the French court and to the cities of Hamburg, Lbeck, and Bremen.
